INT. WORKSHOP - EARLY MORNING

Blueprints cover every wall. The PROTAGONIST, exhausted but focused, circles one impossible detail.

ALLY
You have rebuilt this plan six times.

PROTAGONIST
Six times wrong. This one might survive contact with reality.

A distant alarm bleeds into the room.

EXT. INDUSTRIAL DISTRICT - CONTINUOUS

Sirens echo through narrow streets as workers flood toward the main gate.

PROTAGONIST (V.O.)
Every system fails twice. First in design, then in denial.
